Personalization and sequencing as the central strategic problem  
AGAŌĆÖs living guideline frames therapy selection around comparative efficacy and patient factors rather than a single universal ŌĆ£bestŌĆØ drug. In practice, the treat-to-target paradigm requires individualized monitoring plans that match disease risk, patient preferences, and access constraints. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn11view1Ņłéturn47view1Ņłéturn37view0Ņłü

Safety, infrastructure, and access as limiting factors  
