### Flowchart of research steps for making evidence-based UC decisions

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A[Clarify clinical status\nflare vs remission vs refractory] --> B[Assess severity & extent\nsymptoms + labs + endoscopy as needed]
  B --> C[Define targets\nsymptom control + objective inflammation control]
  C --> D[Select strategy\nadvanced therapy vs conventional options\nbased on risk & history]
  D --> E[Plan monitoring\nbiomarkers (stool/blood) at defined intervals]
  E --> F{Targets met?}
  F -->|Yes| G[Maintain therapy\noptimize adherence\nminimize steroid exposure]
  F -->|No| H[Confirm inflammation\nendoscopy or repeat biomarkers]
  H --> I[Optimize dose\nswitch mechanism\nor consider combination/sequencing]
  I --> E
  D --> J[Supportive care\nnutrition, deficiencies, mental health,\nvaccines, comorbidity management]
  H --> K[If refractory or complicated\nsurgical consultation]
```

This flow reflects the core logic embedded in AGA biomarker guidance, society UC guidelines, and treat-to-target framing: define targets, measure progress objectively, and adjust therapy based on evidence rather than symptoms alone. ŅłĆciteŅłéturn47view0Ņłéturn10search0Ņłéturn48search4Ņłü
